    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "TO : DIRECTOR, FBI DATE: October 2, 1950",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, PHILADELPHIA ATTENTION: MR. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISC REPORTED AT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "PHILADELPHIA ON 9/26/50",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "During the late evening hours of September 26, 1950, two Phila-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "delphia police officers observed a peculiar phenomenon on Vare",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "Boulevard near 26th Street when they saw a round object about",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "six feet in circumference slowly float down to the ground.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "The object had the appearance of a parachute and landed in a field,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "it being so light it did not even depress the weeds in the field.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "The object was lavender in color, described by the officers as",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "dewy, sort of like soap suds, and evaporating within fifteen or",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "twenty minutes after it landed. When touched by the officers, the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "substance composing the object disappeared, leaving nothing but a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "slight sticky substance.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "This matter was reported to this office by the Philadelphia",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "Police and for that matter, was subsequently carried in the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "Philadelphia press as \"Flying Saucer Just Dissolves\".",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Mr. [REDACTED] of the Bureau was telephonically advised of the above",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "by this office and issued instructions that the matter should be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "referred to Air Force Intelligence for handling and any investigation.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Accordingly, Major [REDACTED] of the Philadelphia Office of OSI was",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "telephonically advised of the above and no further action was taken",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "by this office.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
